The game will be available to watch on Prime Video, NFL+, and Yahoo Sports, among other platforms.

name: Big Lots stores closing
summary: Big Lots, a well-known home goods retailer, has announced "going out of business" sales at all of its remaining locations. The company has been facing financial difficulties, including a failed bankruptcy sale. As a result, over 500 corporate employees, including the CEO, will be laid off. Several stores have already closed nationwide, including five in the Baltimore area and multiple locations in Tennessee, Ohio, Kentucky, and the Charlotte area. The company is currently holding going-out-of-business sales at all of its stores, but the exact timing and impact on each location is unclear.

summary: Real Housewives of Potomac star Karen Huger was found guilty of driving under the influence (DUI) and negligent driving charges in Maryland. name: Fair catch free kick
summary: The Los Angeles Chargers made NFL history by scoring the league's first fair-catch kick field goal since 1976, utilizing an obscure rule that allows a team to receive a free kick after a fair catch of a punt or kickoff. The kick was made by Cameron Dicker, marking the first successful conversion of this type since Oakland Raiders player Fred Steinfort in 1976. The move, which caught the Denver Broncos off guard, resulted in three points for the Chargers and highlighted the strategic nuances of the NFL rulebook. This unique play has generated buzz among commentators and fans, showcasing the Chargers' innovative approach to the game.

name: Woody Johnson
summary: The New York Jets have faced controversy under the ownership of Woody Johnson. Reports allege that he interfered in team decisions, including nixing a trade for wide receiver Jerry Jeudy due to his low rating in the "Madden NFL" video game. Johnson's teenage sons have also reportedly influenced critical team decisions. The Athletic and other sources have reported that Johnson demanded to be addressed as "Mr. Ambassador" in 2019. These allegations have raised concerns about Johnson's leadership and the dysfunction within the organization. The Jets have endured a dismal season and are considered one of the "most dysfunctional places imaginable."
